            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "While individual companies can go bankrupt, causing their stock to go to zero, it is extremely unlikely to lose all your money if you are invested in a diversified index fund containing hundreds of large companies."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How do beginners actually make money in stocks?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Beginners make money in two primary ways: capital appreciation (the stock price goes up over time) and dividends (cash payments distributed by the company to shareholders)."
